{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Project Dashboard With Color-Only Status Indicators\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated Perspectives Confirmed\n\n**Escalated for deep review (MEDIUM/HIGH):**\n\n| Perspective | Alarm |\n|---|---|\n| 1. Magnification & Reflow | MEDIUM |\n| 2. Environmental Contrast | HIGH |\n| 5. Keyboard & Motor | MEDIUM |\n| 6. Screen Reader & Semantic | MEDIUM |\n| 7. Cognitive & Neurodivergent | HIGH |\n\n**At LOW \u2014 not reviewed:** 3. Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, 4. Auditory Access.\n\n**Root-cause note carried through all perspectives:** Status for every task is carried by a single 10\u00d710px `<span class=\"status-dot\">` whose only differentiator is `background-color` (fixture L122\u2013125, L249\u2013254). There is no text, icon, shape, pattern, or programmatic name. That one defect surfaces as a distinct finding under three perspectives (Environmental Contrast, Screen Reader, Cognitive) because it blocks three different user groups by three different mechanisms. It is **one fix**, not three \u2014 the summary makes that explicit so severity counts are not mistaken for independent workstreams.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (MEDIUM)\n\n**Checklist:**\n- Reflow to single column at 320px, no horizontal scroll (1.4.10) \u2014 **PASS (exception applies).** The artifact is an 8-column data table. WCAG 1.4.10 exempts \"content requiring two-dimensional layout for usage or meaning,\" and data tables are the canonical example. 2-axis scrolling of the table itself is permitted. Noted with caveat below.\n- Focused elements never obscured by sticky headers/footers (2.4.11) \u2014 **PASS.** No `position: sticky`/`fixed` anywhere in the CSS; nothing can obscure focus.\n- Text scales to 200% without overflow/truncation/broken layout (1.4.4) \u2014 **PASS (with caveat).** Sizes are in `px`, but browser zoom scales `px` text, and there is no AA minimum font size. The 11px base (L193\u2013195) is a low-vision burden, not a 1.4.4 failure. See the 1.4.12 finding for the real text-adaptation defect.\n- Adapts to text-spacing overrides \u2014 1.5 line-height / 2\u00d7 paragraph / 0.12em letter / 0.16em word (1.4.12) \u2014 **FINDING.**\n- Hover/focus content is dismissible, hoverable, persistent (1.4.13) \u2014 **FINDING.**\n\n**Finding:** Description tooltip is CSS `:hover`-only. It never appears on focus, cannot be dismissed with Escape, and is not persistent \u2014 moving the pointer off `.desc-trigger` removes it (`display:none` returns). A screen-magnifier user who pans away from the trigger to read the 220px-wide bubble loses it before finishing.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus (AA)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `.desc-trigger::after { display: none }` (fixture L289\u2013303) with only `.desc-trigger:hover::after { display: block }` (L306\u2013308); no `:focus`/`:focus-within` rule and `.desc-trigger` is a non-focusable `<span>` (L140\u2013142). Red flag \"tooltip disappears before magnifier user can reach it\" is adjacent; held at MAJOR because the *mechanics* are the defect here \u2014 the essential-content blockage is captured as CRITICAL under Perspectives 2/6.\n**Fix:** Replace the hover-only pseudo-element with an accessible disclosure/tooltip: reveal on `hover` AND `focus`, keep it dismissible via Escape, and keep it in the DOM so the pointer can move onto it. Make the trigger focusable (real `<button>`), or render the full description inline.\n\n**Finding:** `white-space: nowrap` on column headers and on `.cell-desc` prevents text-spacing adaptation; combined with `overflow: hidden`, applying a letter/word-spacing override clips content in the description cell.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.12 Text Spacing (AA)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.task-table th { white-space: nowrap }` (L197\u2013202); `.cell-desc { max-width:160px; white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis }` (L276\u2013281). Held at MINOR: data cells (name/owner/due/effort/priority) have no `nowrap` and wrap normally; headers are single short words; the description cell is already truncated by design, so a spacing override loses little *additional* functionality.\n**Fix:** Drop `white-space: nowrap` on headers, or let them wrap. For descriptions, prefer inline wrapping over fixed-width `overflow:hidden` truncation.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 2 \u2014 Environmental Contrast (HIGH)\n\n**Checklist:**\n- Normal text \u2265 4.5:1 (1.4.3) \u2014 **PASS.** Default black text on `#ffffff` (L178\u2013182) \u2248 21:1. Tooltip text `#fff` on `#333` \u2248 12.6:1.\n- Large text \u2265 3:1 (1.4.3) \u2014 **PASS.** `h1` black on white.\n- UI component boundaries/states \u2265 3:1 vs adjacent (1.4.11) \u2014 **FINDING** (selection state) + **FINDING** (progress track, minor).\n- Color is never the sole indicator of meaning (1.4.1) \u2014 **FINDING (CRITICAL).**\n- Instructions don't rely on sensory characteristics alone (1.3.3) \u2014 **PASS.** No prose says \"the green row\"; no instructional text keys on color/position.\n- Functional in forced-colors / Windows High Contrast \u2014 **FINDING** (folded into 1.4.1 below).\n\n**Red flag check:** \"Error state communicated only by red color with no icon or text\" \u2014 **FIRES.** The `blocked` state is a bare red dot (`#d32f2f`, L34, L122\u2013125). Auto-CRITICAL. \"Interactive element indistinguishable from surrounding content in forced-colors\" \u2014 assessed as **not cleanly firing**: rows retain text, borders, and a focus outline in forced-colors, so the *element* stays distinguishable; what is lost is the *selection state* (the tint), which is captured precisely as the 1.4.11 selection finding at MAJOR rather than mechanically escalated.\n\n**Finding:** Task status is conveyed by dot color alone across four states (blocked/at-risk/on-track/not-started), in both the table and the summary bar. No text, icon, shape, or pattern supplements it. Red/green users (protanopia/deuteranopia \u2014 ~8% of males) cannot distinguish `blocked` (`#d32f2f`) from `on-track` (`#2e7d32`) \u2014 the two most operationally opposite states collapse into one. In forced-colors mode all four inline `background-color` dots resolve to a single system color, erasing the differentiator entirely.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.1 Use of Color (A)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** CRITICAL (red flag fired; each dot passing 4.5:1 vs white is exactly why automated tools stay silent \u2014 contrast is not the problem, sole-reliance on hue is)\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `STATUS_COLORS` map (L34\u201339); status cell renders only `<span class=\"status-dot\" style={{ backgroundColor: \u2026 }} />` (L122\u2013125); summary bar repeats the color-only dots with a count and no category label (L151\u2013169); `.status-dot` is a bare colored circle (L249\u2013254).\n**Fix:** Add a non-color indicator to every status: a short text label (\"Blocked\", \"At risk\", \"On track\", \"Not started\") and/or a distinct shape/icon per state (e.g., \u26d4 / \u25b3 / \u25cf / \u25cb). Do not rely on hue as the sole channel. In the summary bar, label each count with its category text. This single change also resolves the Screen-Reader CRITICAL and the Cognitive MAJOR below.\n\n**Finding:** Row-selection state is signaled only by a near-white background tint. `#e3f2fd` vs page `#ffffff` \u2248 1.05:1 and vs an unselected row \u2248 1.05:1 \u2014 far below the 3:1 required to perceive a component state, and it disappears entirely in forced-colors.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast (AA) \u2014 with 1.4.1 Use of Color (A)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.task-row.selected { background-color:#e3f2fd }` is the only selection style (L244\u2013246); no border, outline, weight, or icon change accompanies it.\n**Fix:** Add a non-color, \u22653:1 selection affordance \u2014 a persistent left border/accent bar, a checkmark, or bold weight \u2014 and pair with `aria-selected` (see Perspective 6).\n\n**Finding:** Progress-bar track boundary is imperceptible against the page. `#e0e0e0` track vs `#ffffff` page \u2248 1.3:1, so a low-vision user cannot see the bar's extent.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast (AA)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MINOR (the numeric percentage is shown as adjacent text \u2014 `progress-label`, L134 \u2014 so the information itself is not lost)\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.progress-bar { background:#e0e0e0 }` on white (L256\u2013263).\n**Fix:** Give the track a \u22653:1 border or a darker fill so its boundary is perceivable.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM)\n\n**Checklist:**\n- All interactive elements keyboard-operable (2.1.1) \u2014 **FINDING** (tooltip content) + minor (Space).\n- No keyboard traps (2.1.2) \u2014 **PASS.** Tab/Shift+Tab flow freely.\n- Skip link targets main content (2.4.1) \u2014 **N/A.** Page-level Bypass Blocks; out of scope for a single component fixture.\n- Focus order logical (2.4.3) \u2014 **PASS.** DOM order = 7 header sort buttons, then rows in visual order; sensible.\n- Focus indicator \u22652px, \u22653:1 (2.4.7, 2.4.13) \u2014 **PASS.** `.sort-btn:focus-visible` and `.task-row:focus-visible` both use `2px solid #005fcc` (\u22485.6:1 vs white) (L222\u2013226, L238\u2013241). Genuinely well done.\n- Multi-point gestures have single-pointer alternative (2.5.1) \u2014 **N/A.** None used.\n- Activation on up-event (2.5.2) \u2014 **PASS.** `onClick` fires on pointer-up.\n- Visible label matches accessible name (2.5.3) \u2014 **PASS.** Sort button accessible name = visible column text (icon is `aria-hidden`); label-in-name holds. (Missing *sort-state* exposure is a 4.1.2 issue \u2014 Perspective 6.)\n- Every drag has a click alternative (2.5.7) \u2014 **N/A.** No drag.\n- Targets \u2265 24\u00d724px with adequate spacing (2.5.8) \u2014 **FINDING.**\n- Portrait and landscape both supported (1.3.4) \u2014 **PASS.** No orientation lock.\n\n**Red flag check:** No auto-CRITICAL red flag fires. The unreachable tooltip is *content on hover*, not an interactive control, so \"interactive element unreachable by keyboard\" does not apply; it is scored on impact as MAJOR.\n\n**Finding:** The full task description \u2014 which for several rows is the only text form of the task's status (\"Blocked on vendor credentials\u2026\", \"At risk due to\u2026\") \u2014 is reachable only by mouse hover. `.desc-trigger` is a non-focusable `<span>`, the tooltip has no focus trigger, and the inline text is truncated to 30 characters, cutting off *before* the status word (task 1 inline text ends at \"\u2026gateway API.\" \u2014 \"Blocked\" is hidden). Keyboard-only and touch users cannot reach it.\n**WCAG:** 2.1.1 Keyboard (A)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<span class=\"desc-trigger\" data-tooltip={task.desc}>{task.desc.slice(0,30)}\u2026</span>` (L140\u2013142); hover-only reveal (L306\u2013308). Same control as the Perspective 1 (1.4.13) finding \u2014 one remediation fixes both.\n**Fix:** Make the trigger a focusable `<button>` (or render the description inline/expandable) so keyboard and touch users reach the content; reveal on focus as well as hover.\n\n**Finding:** The header sort control is far below the 24\u00d724px minimum target size. `.sort-btn` has `padding:0` and its icon is a 10\u00d710px glyph, so the hit area is roughly line-height tall (~11\u201314px). The Spacing exception does not rescue it: a 24px-diameter circle centered on the button overlaps the focusable first data row directly beneath, so undersized targets are not adequately separated.\n**WCAG:** 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum) (AA)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Visual Design)\n**Evidence:** `.sort-btn { padding:0 }` (L211\u2013220); `.sort-icon { width:10px; height:10px }` (L229\u2013235). Rows themselves are full-width and pass.\n**Fix:** Increase the button's padding so the interactive box is \u226524\u00d724px (e.g., `padding: 6px 8px`) without shrinking the visible text; ensure adjacent header targets keep clear spacing.\n\n**Finding (minor):** Row `onKeyDown` handles only `Enter`; `Space` does not select and instead scrolls the page, deviating from expected list/grid-item behavior.\n**WCAG:** 2.1.1 Keyboard (A)\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `onKeyDown={e => e.key === 'Enter' && setSelectedRow(task.id)}` (L108).\n**Fix:** Handle `Space` as well (and `preventDefault` to stop scroll) once the row is given a proper interactive role (Perspective 6).\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\n**Checklist:**\n- Landmark regions present/correct (1.3.1) \u2014 **PASS (with page-scope note).** Two labeled `region`s: `<section aria-label=\"Task overview\">` (L71) and `<section class=\"summary-bar\" aria-label=\"Status summary\">` (L151). No `<main>` \u2014 see note.\n- Heading hierarchy logical (2.4.6) \u2014 **PASS.** Single `<h1>` \"Project Dashboard\" (L68), no skipped levels.\n- Informative images have alt / decorative `alt=\"\"` (1.1.1) \u2014 **FINDING (CRITICAL).**\n- DOM order matches visual order (1.3.2) \u2014 **PASS.**\n- Unique descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) \u2014 **N/A.** Document-level; component fixture.\n- Link text describes destination (2.4.4) \u2014 **N/A.** No links.\n- `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) \u2014 **N/A.** Document-level; component fixture.\n- Foreign-language phrases wrapped (3.1.2) \u2014 **N/A.**\n- Every input has associated visible label (3.3.2) \u2014 **N/A.** No form inputs.\n- Errors identify field via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) \u2014 **N/A.** No forms.\n- Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles per APG (4.1.2) \u2014 **FINDING** (sort state) + **FINDING** (row selection).\n- Status messages use `aria-live` (4.1.3) \u2014 **PASS/N-A.** Sort and selection are *states*, correctly exposed via `aria-sort`/`aria-selected` (below), not live-region messages; no live region is warranted here.\n- SPA route changes managed \u2014 **N/A.** No routing.\n\n**Red flag check:** \"No `<main>` landmark\" and \"Missing `lang` on `<html>`\" both target page-level structure and are **out of scope** for a component fixture \u2014 not escalated to CRITICAL (flagging them here would be checklist theater, not user impact). At page-integration time, ensure a `<main>` wraps primary content and `<html lang>` is set. \"Custom widget with no ARIA role\" is present (silent status dot; role-less selectable rows); the CRITICAL below is anchored on 1.1.1 impact rather than a mechanical role tally, and the row issue is scored MAJOR.\n\n**Finding:** The status column is completely silent to assistive technology. `<span class=\"status-dot\">` has no text, no `aria-label`, no `role`, and no `img`+alt \u2014 a screen reader announces an empty cell. A blind user has **no way to determine any task's status**, and the summary bar likewise announces bare numbers (\"1\", \"1\", \"4\"\u2026) with no category. This is the same root defect as the Perspective 2 CRITICAL, viewed through the screen-reader lens: no text alternative for information-bearing non-text content.\n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-text Content (A) \u2014 with 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** Empty `<span class=\"status-dot\" \u2026/>` in the status cell (L122\u2013125); summary items pair `.summary-count` with a label-less dot (L151\u2013169).\n**Fix:** Provide a programmatic text status per row \u2014 visible text label is best; at minimum a visually-hidden text node or `aria-label` on the indicator (e.g., `Status: Blocked`). Label each summary count with its category. Preferred single remediation: render a text+icon status badge, which simultaneously fixes 1.4.1 (Perspective 2) and the Cognitive finding (Perspective 7).\n\n**Finding:** The sortable table exposes no sort state to AT. The active column header carries no `aria-sort=\"ascending|descending\"`, and the only visual cue (\u25b2/\u25bc/\u21c5) is `aria-hidden=\"true\"`. A screen-reader user can press a sort button but cannot perceive which column is sorted or in which direction \u2014 the result of their action is unannounced.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<span class=\"sort-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">{\u2026\u25b2/\u25bc/\u21c5}</span>` (L90\u201392); no `aria-sort` on any `<th>` (L79). Follows APG \"sortable table column header\" only visually.\n**Fix:** Set `aria-sort` on the currently-sorted `<th>` (`ascending`/`descending`; `none` on the rest) and give each sort button an accessible name that includes intent (e.g., \"Sort by Priority, currently ascending\").\n\n**Finding:** Selectable rows have no interactive semantics. `<tr tabIndex={0} onClick>` conveys no role and no selected state \u2014 there is no `aria-selected`, `role=\"row\"`/`aria-selected` in a grid context, nor any indication the row is selectable. AT users don't know rows can be selected or which one is selected (the `.selected` class is invisible to AT and ~1.05:1 visually).\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<tr \u2026 tabIndex={0} onClick={\u2026} onKeyDown={\u2026}>` with `className` toggling `selected` and no ARIA state (L103\u2013109); `.task-row.selected` is style-only (L244\u2013246).\n**Fix:** Give rows an appropriate pattern \u2014 e.g., `role=\"row\"` within a `role=\"grid\"`, or expose `aria-selected={true|false}` on the selectable row \u2014 and pair with the non-color visual selection affordance from Perspective 2.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 7 \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent (HIGH)\n\n**Checklist:**\n- Error messages suggest specific correction (3.3.3) \u2014 **N/A.** No forms/errors.\n- Multi-step forms don't re-ask (3.3.7) \u2014 **N/A.**\n- Auth allows paste/autofill, no puzzle (3.3.8) \u2014 **N/A.**\n- Navigation in same relative position across pages (3.2.3) \u2014 **N/A.** Single view.\n- Same-function components consistent (3.2.4) \u2014 **PASS.** Consistent within the view.\n- Help mechanism consistent location (3.2.6) \u2014 **N/A.** None.\n- Focus does not auto-trigger context change (3.2.1) \u2014 **PASS.** Focusing a row/button does nothing until activation.\n- Changing a control value does not auto-submit (3.2.2) \u2014 **N/A.** No form controls.\n- Destructive actions have undo/confirmation (3.3.4) \u2014 **N/A.** No destructive actions.\n- More than one way to reach a page (2.4.5) \u2014 **N/A.** Page-level.\n- Personal-data inputs have `autocomplete` (1.3.5) \u2014 **N/A.** No inputs.\n- Timeout warnings \u226520s (2.2.1) \u2014 **N/A.** No timeouts.\n- Avoids unexplained jargon/undefined abbreviations/complex sentences \u2014 **FINDING** (color legend, AA) + **ENHANCEMENT** (abbreviations, AAA).\n\n**Neurodivergent-specific:** predictable layout, no unprompted shifts \u2014 **PASS** (reorder happens only on user sort). Clear visual hierarchy \u2014 dense 11px / 8-column layout is taxing but sets no AA bar; noted as observation. No autoplay/unprompted modals \u2014 **PASS.** Instructions don't rely on memory \u2014 **FINDING** (the color legend must be memorized).\n\n**Red flag check:** No auto-CRITICAL red flag fires (no CAPTCHA, no paste-block, no redundant re-entry, no unconfirmed destructive action).\n\n**Finding:** The color-coded status system provides no text labels and no persistent legend anywhere on screen, forcing users to memorize a four-way color key (red=blocked, amber=at-risk, green=on-track, blue=not-started) and re-derive it on every glance. The summary bar compounds this: counts sit beside color-only dots with no category text, so the tallies are meaningless without decoding color from memory. For users with working-memory or cognitive-load sensitivities this is a real barrier, not a preference.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.1 Use of Color (A) \u2014 cognitive-load manifestation of the shared root defect\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Content Author + UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** No legend/key in the markup; status conveyed only by `STATUS_COLORS` dots (L34\u201339, L122\u2013125); summary bar counts with unlabeled dots (L151\u2013169).\n**Fix:** Show the status word in-line on each row, and/or provide a persistent, always-visible legend near the table. Label summary counts with their category text. (Resolved by the same text+icon status badge that fixes Perspectives 2 and 6.)\n\n**Finding:** Undefined abbreviations increase reading load \u2014 Effort values \"L/M/S\" and Priority values \"P1/P2/P3\" appear with no expansion or key; owner initials (JL/MK/SP/RP) are also unexplained.\n**WCAG:** 3.1.4 Abbreviations (AAA)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** ENHANCEMENT (AAA \u2014 reported, never escalated per protocol)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `cell-effort`/`cell-priority` render raw `{task.effort}`/`{task.priority}` (L114, L116); no `<abbr>` or legend.\n**Fix:** Expand on first use or provide a key/tooltip (e.g., `<abbr title=\"Large\">L</abbr>`, \"P1 = highest priority\"). Optional but valuable for the target group.\n\n**Observation (not a WCAG finding):** The overall density \u2014 11px cells (L193\u2013195), 8 columns, tight 5\u20136px padding, small progress text (10px, L271\u2013274) \u2014 raises cognitive and low-vision load. No AA criterion sets a density or font-size floor, so this is flagged as design guidance, not a violation: consider a larger base size and more row spacing.\n\n---\n\n## A11y Evidence Findings (new CRITICAL/MAJOR \u2014 contract blocks for tracker traceability)\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: status_conveyed_by_color_alone\nfingerprint: 1c4a10d32f2fc0a1\nsource: perspective-audit Environmental Contrast checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.1 Use of Color (A)\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 1.4.1 is WCAG 2.0 Level A, incorporated by Revised Section 508\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: environmental_contrast=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM, cognitive_neurodivergent=HIGH\nevidence: STATUS_COLORS map (fixture L34-39); status cell renders only `<span class=\"status-dot\" style={{backgroundColor}}/>` (L122-125); summary bar dots unlabeled (L151-169)\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Also: view in a grayscale/deuteranopia simulator \u2014 blocked (#d32f2f) and on-track (#2e7d32) become indistinguishable; enable forced-colors \u2014 all four dots collapse to one system color.\nexpected_behavior: Each status distinguishable without relying on color \u2014 text label and/or shape/icon per state\nactual_behavior: Hue is the sole differentiator across four states; each dot passes 4.5:1 vs white so automated contrast checks stay green\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: status_no_text_alternative_screen_reader\nfingerprint: 1a11e5d0be51015c\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.1.1 Non-text Content (A); 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 1.1.1 and 4.1.2 are WCAG 2.0 Level A\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM (updated to HIGH on deep review), environmental_contrast=HIGH\nevidence: Empty `<span class=\"status-dot\">` with no text/aria-label/role (L122-125); summary counts label-less (L151-169)\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Also: navigate the status column with a screen reader \u2014 the cell is announced empty.\nexpected_behavior: Programmatic text status per row (visible text, visually-hidden text, or aria-label)\nactual_behavior: Status cell is silent; blind users cannot determine any task's status\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: description_tooltip_hover_only\nfingerprint: 14d1300be7cff0a2\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow + Keyboard & Motor checklists\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.13 Content on Hover or Focus (AA); 2.1.1 Keyboard (A)\nsection_508_fpc_context: 2.1.1 in scope (WCAG 2.0 A); 1.4.13 is a WCAG 2.1 criterion, not in the WCAG 2.0 508 baseline\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=MEDIUM, keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: `.desc-trigger::after` hidden by default, shown only on `:hover` (L289-303, L306-308); non-focusable `<span>` trigger; inline text truncated to 30 chars before the status word (L140-142)\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Also: Tab to the row \u2014 full description is unreachable; hover then move pointer away \u2014 tooltip vanishes with no Escape/persistence.\nexpected_behavior: Content available on focus and hover, dismissible via Escape, persistent/hoverable\nactual_behavior: Mouse-hover only; keyboard/touch/magnifier users cannot read the (often status-bearing) description\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: row_selection_no_noncolor_indicator\nfingerprint: 14b11e3f2fd05e1c\nsource: perspective-audit Environmental Contrast + Screen Reader checklists\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast (AA); 1.4.1 Use of Color (A); 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\nsection_508_fpc_context: 1.4.1/4.1.2 in scope (WCAG 2.0 A); 1.4.11 is WCAG 2.1, not in the 508 baseline\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: environmental_contrast=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `.task-row.selected { background-color:#e3f2fd }` only (L244-246) \u22481.05:1 vs white/unselected; no aria-selected on `<tr>` (L103-109)\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Select a row \u2014 visual change ~1.05:1; forced-colors removes it; no aria-selected announced.\nexpected_behavior: Selection shown with a \u22653:1 non-color affordance and exposed via aria-selected\nactual_behavior: Near-invisible tint is the sole indicator, invisible to low-vision, forced-colors, and AT users\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: sort_button_target_under_24px\nfingerprint: 2c5b8100a1105128\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum) (AA)\nsection_508_fpc_context: 2.5.8 is a WCAG 2.2 criterion \u2014 not in the WCAG 2.0 508 baseline\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: `.sort-btn { padding:0 }` (L211-220); `.sort-icon { width:10px; height:10px }` (L229-235); ~11-14px hit area; 24px circle overlaps focusable first row, defeating the Spacing exception\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Measure the sort control hit box in DevTools.\nexpected_behavior: Interactive target \u226524\u00d724 CSS px, or undersized with sufficient spacing\nactual_behavior: Sort target is well under 24\u00d724px with insufficient separation from the row below\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: sort_state_not_exposed_to_at\nfingerprint: 41205a1a50c70b0e\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A); WAI-ARIA APG sortable table column header\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 4.1.2 is WCAG 2.0 Level A\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on the \u25b2/\u25bc/\u21c5 icon (L90-92); no `aria-sort` on any `<th>` (L79)\nreproduction_steps: Source review only. Activate a sort button with a screen reader \u2014 sorted column/direction is unannounced.\nexpected_behavior: aria-sort on the active header; sort buttons named with column + current direction\nactual_behavior: Sort state is visual-only and aria-hidden; AT users cannot perceive the result of sorting\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Project Dashboard With Color-Only Status Indicators (React component + CSS)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Magnification & Reflow (MEDIUM), Environmental Contrast (HIGH), Keyboard & Motor (MEDIUM), Screen Reader & Semantic (MEDIUM), Cognitive & Neurodivergent (HIGH)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 2 |\n| MAJOR | 6 |\n| MINOR | 3 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 1 |\n\n> **Shared root cause:** The two CRITICALs (1.4.1 color-only status; 1.1.1 silent status column) and the Cognitive MAJOR (memorized color legend) are **one defect through three lenses** \u2014 a status indicator with no non-color, text-based channel. A single remediation (text + icon status badge, with labeled summary counts and a persistent legend) resolves all three. Counting them separately reflects three blocked user groups, not three fixes.\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone passed cleanly. Every escalated perspective produced at least one finding. Notable *strengths* observed: correct heading structure and single `h1`; real `<table>`/`<thead>`/`<tbody>` with `scope=\"col\"`; two labeled landmark regions; and well-formed, sufficient-contrast focus indicators on both sort buttons and rows (a genuine bright spot \u2014 the keyboard *reachability* and *visibility* of focus are done right; the gaps are in *what* is exposed and *target size*).\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- Status column silent to screen readers \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.1.1 / 4.1.2\n- Description tooltip hover-only, keyboard-inaccessible \u2014 Keyboard & Motor / Magnification \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.1.1 / 1.4.13\n- Sort button target under 24\u00d724px \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.5.8\n- Sort state not exposed to AT (no aria-sort) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2\n- Selectable rows lack aria-selected/role \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2\n- Row keydown handles Enter but not Space \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MINOR \u2014 2.1.1\n\n**Visual Design**\n- Status conveyed by color alone (dots) \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.4.1\n- Row selection indicated only by ~1.05:1 tint \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.11 / 1.4.1\n- Progress-bar track boundary <3:1 vs page \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.11\n- `nowrap` headers/description clip under text-spacing override \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.12\n\n**UX Design + Content Author**\n- Color status has no text labels or persistent legend (memorization burden) \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.1\n- Undefined abbreviations L/M/S, P1/P2/P3, owner initials \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 ENHANCEMENT \u2014 3.1.4 (AAA)\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\nMost findings are code-level and confirmable from source. Content decisions to confirm with the team:\n- Exact status label wording for each state (\"Blocked\"/\"At risk\"/\"On track\"/\"Not started\" vs project vocabulary) `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n- Whether the target audience needs abbreviation expansions (Effort L/M/S, Priority P1/P2/P3) and, if so, their definitions `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n- Whether the full task description is essential content (it carries the only textual status reasoning for some rows); if essential, the tooltip fix is required, not optional `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 Two CRITICAL findings (status conveyed by color alone; status column silent to screen readers) prevent color-blind, low-vision/forced-colors, and screen-reader users from determining any task's status, which is the dashboard's primary purpose. Do not ship until the status indicator carries a non-color, programmatic-text channel. Address the six MAJOR findings (tooltip keyboard access, target size, aria-sort, aria-selected + non-color selection, progress track contrast) in the same pass before re-test.\n",
